Package org.openscience.cdk.geometry.cip

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ILigand
    Concept of a ligand in CIP terms, reflecting a side chain of a central atom that can have precedence over another.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CIPTool
    Tool to help determine the R,S and stereochemistry definitions of a subset of the CIP rules [Cahn, R.S. and Ingold, C. and Prelog, V., Specification of Molecular Chirality, Angew. Chem. Int. Ed., 1966, 5:385-415].
    ImplicitHydrogenLigand
    Subclass of Ligand to which no further recursion must be applied.
    Ligand
    Concept of a ligand in CIP terms, reflecting a side chain of a central atom that can have precedence over another.
    VisitedAtoms
    Helper class for the CIPTool to keep track of which atoms have already been visited.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CIPTool.CIP_CHIRALITY
    Enumeration with the two tetrahedral chiralities defined by the CIP schema.
